  "texts": [
    "1, Article.",
    "Publication date: January 2025.Table 1.",
    "An overview of the primary discoveries presented in our work.",
    "We summarize our findings in the second column as \"our findings\", and verify findings in existing literature as \"re-validated findings\".",
    "AspectOur Findings Re-validated Findings LLMs• The long-chain reasoning capabilities and slow-thinking process of LLMs are optimized for Mathematics and coding tasks, which may not be suitable for the recommendation task.• The larger the parameter scale, the better the ability, while a longer maximum context length leads to worse recommendations.• Fine-tuning all parameters of LLMs is more effective than parameter-efficient fine-tuning such as LoRA, but more training time is required."
  ]
}